    • Method Detail

      • createProcessOrder

        void createProcessOrder(ProcessOrder theProcessOrder)
        Create and schedule a new ProcessOrder. The given process order must have a valid process name.
        Parameters:
        theProcessOrder - the process order configuration
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if given process order has id != 0
        IllegalArgumentException - if given process order has no process name

      • createProcessOrder

        void createProcessOrder(ProcessOrder theProcessOrder,
                      String parameter)
        Look up processes with given parameter and schedule the given ProcessOrder for each associated process.
        Parameters:
        theProcessOrder - the process order configuration
        parameter - the parameter used to lookup associated processes
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if given process order has id != 0
        IllegalArgumentException - if given parameter is null or empty and process order has no process name

      • rescheduleProcessOrder

        void rescheduleProcessOrder(long processOrderId)
        Reschedules the process order with given processOrderId regardless of the state of the process order. This can lead to a inconsistent state of a process being currently executed.
        Parameters:
        processOrderId -
